        <div class="card">

            <h2>What is ToU/ToD ?</h2>

            <p>
                <i>Time of Use (ToU) / Time of Day (ToD)</i> is a pricing system where the cost of electricity
                changes depending on the time of the day. During peak hours, when many people use electricity,
                the price is higher. During off-peak hours, when demand is lower, the price is cheaper.
            </p>

        </div>


        <div class="card">

            <h2>Where are ToU and ToD used?</h2>

            <p>
                <i>Time of Use (ToU) pricing</i> is widely used in many European and American countries to
                manage electricity demand. Countries such as the United States, the United Kingdom, Germany,
                France, and Italy actively use ToU tariffs, especially in homes with smart meters, to
                encourage consumers to shift electricity usage to off-peak hours.
            </p>

            <p>
                In India, a similar concept called <i>Time of Day (ToD) pricing</i> is implemented mainly for
                commercial and industrial consumers. It is actively used in states such as Maharashtra,
                Gujarat, Karnataka, and Delhi, where electricity prices vary during peak and off-peak
                periods to reduce grid congestion and promote efficient energy usage.
            </p>

        </div>


        <div class="card">

            <h2>The Problem We Solve</h2>

            <p>
                Electricity prices change throughout the day under ToU/ToD pricing, but most people are not
                aware of these price variations or do not manually adjust their appliance usage based on
                cheaper time periods. As a result, many appliances run during expensive peak hours, leading
                to higher electricity bills and increased load on the power grid.
            </p>

            <p>
                Our system solves this problem by automatically scheduling and controlling household
                appliances based on electricity price and user preferences, helping users reduce electricity
                costs and use energy more efficiently.
            </p>

        </div>

